nts have varied in volume, intensity, and durability across space and time. Beginning with an original typology of Zionism and a new take on its relationship to colonialism, Penslar then examines the emotions that have shaped Zionist sensibilities and practices over the course of the movement’s history. The resulting portrait of Zionism reconfigures how we understand Jewish identity amidst continuing debates on the role of nationalism in the modern world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aLand settlementzPalestine. 0aZionismxHistory. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  anationialism, jew, judiasm, isreal, palestine, arab, zion, zionisn, migration, immigration, emmigration, occupation, identity, jewish identity, politics, war, public policy, political science, history, religion, nation, culture, jewish studies, jewish history, Israeli, Palestinian.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishz978311131913108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023z9783111318189oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079130340uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978081357612140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813576121423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780813576121/original  a978-3-11-079130-3  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131913-1  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEGb2023  aZDB-23-DGGb2023